{"title_page": "Kevin Moon (singer)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = Kevin Moon\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = \n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = Kevin Moon\n| alias            = Kevine\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1998|02|23}}\n| birth_place      = [[Gwangju]], South Korea\n| origin           = \n| death_date       =\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = [[K-pop]]\n| occupation       = Singer\n| instrument       = Piano, guitar\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[List of Kakao M labels#Cre.ker Entertainment|Cre.ker]]|[[Sony Music Entertainment Japan|Sony Japan]]|[[NetEase Music|NetEase]]}}\n| associated_acts  = [[The Boyz (South Korean band)|The Boyz]]\n| website          =\n| module           = {{Infobox Korean name\n|child  = yes\n|hangul = {{linktext|\ubb38|\ud615\uc11c}}\n|hanja  = {{linktext|\u6587|\u70af|\u66f8 }}\n|rr     = Moon Hyeong-seo\n|mr     = Mun Hy\u014fngs\u014f}}\n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\n'''Kevin Moon''' (born February 23, 1998), known professionally as '''Kevin,''' is a [[Korean Canadians|Korean Canadian]] singer and artist signed with [[Kakao M]] under [[List of Kakao M labels#Cre.ker Entertainment|Cre.ker Entertainment]]. He is currently best known as a member and main vocalist of boy group [[The Boyz (South Korean band)|The Boyz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002941459|title=\"\ud504\ub4c02\u00b7\uace0\ub4f1\ub798\ud37c\u00b7K\ud31d6 \ucd9c\uc2e0\"\u2026\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \ub4dc\ub9bc\ud300 \uacb0\uc131|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSince 2018, Kevin has also been the host of the TV show [[Simply K-Pop]] alongside his bandmate, Jacob.\n\n== Early life and education ==\n{{unsourced BLP section|date=December 2019}}\nKevin was born in [[Gwangju]], [[South Korea]] and raised in [[Canada]] around the [[Coquitlam]] area. He graduated from [[Burnaby Mountain Secondary School]] and then briefly attended the [[University of British Columbia]] in 2016 before leaving Canada to pursue a career in music in South Korea. He has lived in Vancouver, Canada, for 14 years.\n\n== Career ==\n=== 2016\u20132017: K-pop Star 6 and early career===\nKevin began his professional musical career in 2016 at 18 years old auditioning as a contestant for the [[Kpop Star 6|sixth season of ''K-pop Star'']], a South Korean reality television singing competition show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=215&aid=0000563645|website=entertain.naver.com|title=\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, 'K\ud31d6' \ucf00\ube48\ubd80\ud130 'IOI\uc758 \ub0a8\uc790' \uc601\ud6c8\uae4c\uc9c0 \uba64\ubc84\ub4e4 \ud654\ub824\ud55c \uc774\ub825 \ud654\uc81c :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 TV\uc5f0\uc608|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002941459|website=entertain.naver.com|title=\"\ud504\ub4c02\u00b7\uace0\ub4f1\ub798\ud37c\u00b7K\ud31d6 \ucd9c\uc2e0\"\u2026\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \ub4dc\ub9bc\ud300 \uacb0\uc131 :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 TV\uc5f0\uc608|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> Following his elimination from the program he recorded his first single \"Half\" under his Korean name '''Moon Hyeongseo''', which released in April 2017 as an OST for the drama [[Saimdang, Light's Diary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003520379|website=entertain.naver.com|title='K\ud31d6' \ubb38\ud615\uc11c, '\uc0ac\uc784\ub2f9' OST\ub85c \uccab \uc194\ub85c\uace1 19\uc77c \uacf5\uac1c|accessdate=September 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u2013present: The Boyz===\n{{main| The Boyz (South Korean band)}}\n\nIn early July, music label [[List of Kakao M labels#Cre.ker Entertainment|Cre.ker Entertainment]] started releasing videos of artists joining their newest boy group, with a video of Kevin singing released on their social media on July 10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Creker_THEBOYZ/status/883657071870091265|title=\ud06c\ub798\ucee4\uc988(Cre.kerz) [\uc5f0\uc2b5\uc0dd\ud328\uce58(TRAINEE PAPARAZZI)] \ud06c\ub798\ucee4\uc988 \uc74c\uc0c9\ubcf4\ubb3c \ucf00\ube48(KEVIN) \ub77c\uc774\ube0c \u25b6}}{{Primary source inline|date=September 2019}}</ref> On July 18, he was confirmed to be in the final lineup of the group, The Boyz.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Creker_THEBOYZ/status/887507737604636672|title=\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988(THE BOYZ) X DAZED PROFILE FILM No. 06 \ucf00\ube48(KEVIN)}}{{Primary source inline|date=September 2019}}</ref>\n\nFrom August 23 to October 11, Kevin joined his second reality show ''Flower Boy Snack Shop (\uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8 \ubd84\uc2dd\uc9d1)'', this time joining his bandmates and releasing the song \"I'm Your Boy\" during the finale episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000276093|website=entertain.naver.com|title='\uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8 \ubd84\uc2dd\uc9d1', \uc624\ub298(23\uc77c) \uccab \ubc29\uc1a1... \uad8c\ud601\uc218 \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988 13\ubc88\uc9f8 \uba64\ubc84\ub85c \uc601\uc785? :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 TV\uc5f0\uc608|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003635260|website=entertain.naver.com|title='\uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8\ubd84\uc2dd\uc9d1' \uc601\uc5c5\uc885\ub8cc\u2025\ud300\uc6cc\ud06c\ub85c \ud558\ub098\ub41c \ub9cc\ub2a5\ub3cc(ft,\ud32c\uc1a1)&#91;\uc885\ud569&#93; :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 TV\uc5f0\uc608|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/217361|title=&lt;\uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8 \ubd84\uc2dd\uc9d1&gt; \uc601\uc5c5 \ub9c8\uce5c \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \ud2b9\ubcc4\ud55c \ub178\ub798 \uc120\ubb3c \uc804\uaca9 \uacf5\uac1c! &#124; MBC \uc5f0\uc608 \uc2a4\ud3ec\uce20|website=enews.imbc.com|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> On December 6, the group officially debuted, selling out all 4,000 seats debut showcase where they released their first [[extended play]] ''The First'' and its lead single \"Boy\".<ref name=\"boy\">{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003188892&lfrom=kakao&lfrom=twitter|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd]\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc624\ub298(6\uc77c) \uac00\uc694\uacc4 \ub370\ubdd4\u2026\uc790\uc2e0 \uc788\ub294 \ucd9c\uc0ac\ud45c|access-date=December 7, 2017|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2017/12/01/2017120100801.html|title=\"\uc5ed\uc2dc \uad34\ubb3c\uc2e0\uc778\"\u2026\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \ub370\ubdd4 \uc1fc\ucf00\uc774\uc2a4 LTE\uae09 \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4|website=news.chosun.com|language=ko|access-date=August 8, 2019}}</ref> Kevin's family came from Canada to attend the showcase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1094971wpp/watch-boyz-burst-tears-behind-scenes-debut-showcase|title=The Boyz Burst into Tears Behind The Scenes Of Debut Showcase|website=}}</ref>\n\nThroughout 2018, Kevin continued to release music with The Boyz throughout 2018, releasing two more extended plays, a special digital single and a single album.<ref name=\"giddyup\">{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=052&aid=0001131644|title= [Y\ud604\uc7a5] \"\ub9e4\ub825 \ub4dc\ub7ec\ub0bc \uac83\" \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, 2018 \uaf43\uae38 \ub2ec\ub9b4\uae4c(\uc885\ud569)|access-date=April 3, 2018|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003821641|title=\"\uc774\ubc88\uc5d4 \uc5ec\ub984\uc18c\ub144\"..\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc624\ub298(12\uc77c) \uc2e0\uace1 '\uc9c0\ud0ac\uac8c' \ubc1c\ud45c|date=July 12, 2018|accessdate=July 13, 2018|language=ko|work=OSEN|publisher=[[Naver]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=444477#_enliple|title='\ucef4\ubc31 D-DAY' \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988(THE BOYZ), '\uc9c0\ud0ac\uac8c' \uc568\ubc94 \ucee4\ubc84 \uc804\uaca9 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026'\uccad\ub7c9\u7f8e \uac00\ub4dd'|date=July 12, 2018|accessdate=July 13, 2018|language=ko|publisher=Topstarnews|author=Yang Jin-jeong}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=088&aid=0000552119|title=\"\uc2e0\uc778\uc0c1 2\uad00\uc655\uc744 \ub118\uc5b4..\"'\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988' \uc644\uc804\uccb4 \ucef4\ubc31, \uc2e0\uace1 'Right Here' \uc74c\uc6d0\u00b7MV \uacf5\uac1c|work=Naver|language=ko|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1262547wpp/boyz-gives-magical-look-november-comeback-shares-details|title=The Boyz Gears Up For 'The Only' Comeback With Aesthetic Teaser Video|website=soompi.com}}</ref> On May 31, 2018, Kevin joined the English-language South Korean TV show [[Simply K-Pop]] as a permanent host, together with his fellow Korean Canadian bandmate Jacob. He also won several awards with The Boyz, including the \"Rookie Award\" at the Soribada Best K-Music Awards and the \"Best New Male Artist Award\" at the [[2018 Melon Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1271995wpp/winners-2018-melon-music-awards|title=Winners of the 2018 Melon Music Awards|work=Soompi|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"soribadaawards\">{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=440&aid=0000018203|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5\uc601\uc0c1] '\uc18c\ub9ac\ubc14\ub2e4 \uc5b4\uc6cc\uc988' \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc2e0\ud55c\ub958 \ub8e8\ud0a4\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1 \"\ubaa8\ub450 \ub354\ube44\ub4e4 \ub355\ubd84\uc774\uc5d0\uc694\"|work=Naver|language=ko|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Kevin went on tour with The Boyz' Asia fan concert tour ''\"The Castle\"'', with dates in South Korea, Japan, Hong Kong, Singapore, Indonesia, Thailand, Taiwan, and the Philippines.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003370160|title=\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \u4e9e\ud22c\uc5b4 \ud655\uc815\u2026\ud32c\ucf58 '\ub354 \uce90\uc2ac' 8\uac1c\uad6d \uac1c\ucd5c |access-date=January 18, 2019|language=ko}}</ref> The group released their second single album ''Bloom Bloom'' and its lead single \"Bloom Bloom\" on April 29, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1111132103|title=\ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc624\ub298(29\uc77c) \uc2e0\uace1 '\ube14\ub8f8\ube14\ub8f8'\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31..V\ub77c\uc774\ube0c \uc0dd\uc911\uacc4[\uacf5\uc2dd] |work=osen|language=ko|accessdate=April 29, 2019}}</ref> On 7 May, Kevin received his first-ever [[Music programs of South Korea#Chart Systems|music show win]] on [[SBS MTV]]'s ''[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]]'' with The Boyz.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000988059|title='\ub354\uc1fc' \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988, \uc5d4\ud50c\ub77c\uc789\u00b7\ubc15\ubd04 \uc81c\uce58\uace0 1\uc704 \ucc28\uc9c0 [\uc885\ud569] |work=Naver|language=ko|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{main|The Boyz (South Korean band)#Discography}}\n\n=== Soundtrack appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n! scope=\"col\" |Album\n|-\n|2017\n! scope=\"row\" |\"Half\"\n| ''[[Saimdang, Light's Diary]]'' OST\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moon, Kevin}}\n<!--- Categories --->\n[[Category:Korean-language singers of Canada]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian musicians of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:South Korean television personalities]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|